Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
verifyTieCell(25.10)                                      verifyTieCell(25.10)

Name
       verifyTieCell - Checks tie cell connections

Syntax
       verifyTieCell

       [-help]

       [-noTieCell <filename>]

       [-powerDomain <string>]

       [-report <filename>]

       Checks tie cell connections. verifyTieCell honors the tie high/low cell
       list  from  setTieHiLoMode  -cell  and  checks  whether  or not the tie
       high/low nets are connected to the tie high/low cells.

       Use this command after using addTieHiLo to  add  instances  of  tie-off
       cells to the logical hierarchy of the design.

       The expected flow is as follows:

              * Specify  the  tie  cell names and other settings with the set-
                TieHiLoMode command.

              * Add tie high/low cells with addTieHiLo.

              * Run verifyTieCell to check whether tie  cell  connections  are
                correct.

       Violations can be viewed in Violation Browser.

Parameters
       -help  Prints  a  brief  description that includes the type and default
              information for each verifyTieCell parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and  all  its  parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man verifyTieCell

       -noTieCell <filename>
              Specifies  a  file  containing  exception  list  of instance/pin
              names. Use this parameter  to  specify  the  instance/pins  that
              should not have any tie cell connections.

              The  file  should  list  instance and pin names in the following
              format:

              <instance_name/pin_name>

       -powerDomain <string>
              Specifies the power domain name to be checked.

       -report <filename>
              Specifies the report file for recording tie cell violations.  By
              default, the report is saved as <designName>.tie.rpt.

Examples
              * The  following  commands  check the tie cell to assess if TIEH
                and TIEL are inserted for tie nets. If the dontTouch  instance
                does not have a tie cell, violation will not be detected:

                setTieHiLoMode -cell {TIEH TIEL} -honorDontTouch true

                verifyTieCell -report vtc.rpt

              * The  following commands will check if inst or pin in inst.list
                has a tie cell. If it happens, a violation will be detected:

                setTieHiLoMode -cell {TIEH TIEL}

                verifyTieCell -noTieCell inst.list -report vtc.rpt

Related Information
              * addTieHiLo

              * setTieHiLoMode

              * "Verifying Tie Cells" in the Identifying  and  Viewing  Viola-
                tions chapter of User Guide.

